9#define kEmptyHashValue 0
10#define kMaxValForNormalize ((UInt32)0xFFFFFFFF)
11#define kNormalizeStepMin (1 << 10) /* it must be power of 2 */
12#define kNormalizeMask (~(kNormalizeStepMin - 1))
13#define kMaxHistorySize ((UInt32)3 << 30)
14
15#define kStartMaxLen 3

17static void LzInWindow_Free(CMatchFinder *p, ISzAlloc *alloc)
18{
19 if (!p->directInput)
20 {
21 alloc->Free(alloc, p->bufferBase);
22 p->bufferBase = 0;
23 }
24}
25
26/* keepSizeBefore + keepSizeAfter + keepSizeReserv must be < 4G) */
27
28static int LzInWindow_Create(CMatchFinder *p, UInt32 keepSizeReserv, ISzAlloc *alloc)
29{
30 UInt32 blockSize = p->keepSizeBefore + p->keepSizeAfter + keepSizeReserv;
31 if (p->directInput)
32 {
33 p->blockSize = blockSize;
34 return 1;
35 }
36 if (p->bufferBase == 0 || p->blockSize != blockSize)
37 {
38 LzInWindow_Free(p, alloc);
39 p->blockSize = blockSize;
40 p->bufferBase = (Byte *) alloc->Alloc(alloc, (size_t) blockSize);
41 }
42 return (p->bufferBase != 0);
43}

45Byte *MatchFinder_GetPointerToCurrentPos(CMatchFinder *p)
46{
47 return p->buffer;

49Byte MatchFinder_GetIndexByte(CMatchFinder *p, Int32 index)
50{
51 return p->buffer[index];

54UInt32 MatchFinder_GetNumAvailableBytes(CMatchFinder *p)
55{
56 return p->streamPos - p->pos;
57}

59void MatchFinder_ReduceOffsets(CMatchFinder *p, UInt32 subValue)
60{
61 p->posLimit -= subValue;
62 p->pos -= subValue;
63 p->streamPos -= subValue;
64}

66static void MatchFinder_ReadBlock(CMatchFinder *p)
67{
68 if (p->streamEndWasReached || p->result != SZ_OK)
69 return;
70 if (p->directInput)
71 {
72 UInt32 curSize = 0xFFFFFFFF - p->streamPos;
73 if (curSize > p->directInputRem)
74 curSize = (UInt32) p->directInputRem;
75 p->directInputRem -= curSize;
76 p->streamPos += curSize;
77 if (p->directInputRem == 0)
78 p->streamEndWasReached = 1;
79 return;
80 }
81 for (;;)
82 {
83 Byte *dest = p->buffer + (p->streamPos - p->pos);
84 size_t size = (p->bufferBase + p->blockSize - dest);
85 if (size == 0)
86 return;
87 p->result = p->stream->Read(p->stream, dest, &size);
88 if (p->result != SZ_OK)
89 return;
90 if (size == 0)
91 {
92 p->streamEndWasReached = 1;
93 return;
94 }
95 p->streamPos += (UInt32) size;
96 if (p->streamPos - p->pos > p->keepSizeAfter)
97 return;
98 }
99}
100
101void MatchFinder_MoveBlock(CMatchFinder *p)
102{
103 memmove(p->bufferBase,
104 p->buffer - p->keepSizeBefore,
105 (size_t)(p->streamPos - p->pos + p->keepSizeBefore));
106 p->buffer = p->bufferBase + p->keepSizeBefore;
107}
108
109int MatchFinder_NeedMove(CMatchFinder *p)
110{
111 if (p->directInput)
112 return 0;
113 /* if (p->streamEndWasReached) return 0; */
114 return ((size_t) (p->bufferBase + p->blockSize - p->buffer) <= p->keepSizeAfter);
115}
116
117void MatchFinder_ReadIfRequired(CMatchFinder *p)
118{
119 if (p->streamEndWasReached)
120 return;
121 if (p->keepSizeAfter >= p->streamPos - p->pos)
122 MatchFinder_ReadBlock(p);
123}
124
125static void MatchFinder_CheckAndMoveAndRead(CMatchFinder *p)
126{
127 if (MatchFinder_NeedMove(p))
128 MatchFinder_MoveBlock(p);
129 MatchFinder_ReadBlock(p);
130}

132static void MatchFinder_SetDefaultSettings(CMatchFinder *p)
133{
134 p->cutValue = 32;
135 p->btMode = 1;
136 p->numHashBytes = 4;
137 p->bigHash = 0;
138}
139
140#define kCrcPoly 0xEDB88320
141
142void MatchFinder_Construct(CMatchFinder *p)
143{
144 UInt32 i;
145 p->bufferBase = 0;
146 p->directInput = 0;
147 p->hash = 0;
148 MatchFinder_SetDefaultSettings(p);
149
150 for (i = 0; i < 256; i++)
151 {
152 UInt32 r = i;
153 int j;
154 for (j = 0; j < 8; j++)
155 r = (r >> 1) ^ (kCrcPoly & ~((r & 1) - 1));
156 p->crc[i] = r;
157 }
158}

160static void MatchFinder_FreeThisClassMemory(CMatchFinder *p, ISzAlloc *alloc)
161{
162 alloc->Free(alloc, p->hash);
163 p->hash = 0;
164}
165
166void MatchFinder_Free(CMatchFinder *p, ISzAlloc *alloc)
167{
168 MatchFinder_FreeThisClassMemory(p, alloc);
169 LzInWindow_Free(p, alloc);
170}

172static CLzRef* AllocRefs(UInt32 num, ISzAlloc *alloc)
173{
174 size_t sizeInBytes = (size_t) num * sizeof(CLzRef);
175 if (sizeInBytes / sizeof(CLzRef) != num)
176 return 0;
177 return (CLzRef *) alloc->Alloc(alloc, sizeInBytes);
178}
179
180int MatchFinder_Create(CMatchFinder *p, UInt32 historySize, UInt32 keepAddBufferBefore, UInt32 matchMaxLen, UInt32 keepAddBufferAfter,
181 ISzAlloc *alloc)
182{
183 UInt32 sizeReserv;
184 if (historySize > kMaxHistorySize)
185 {
186 MatchFinder_Free(p, alloc);
187 return 0;
188 }
189 sizeReserv = historySize >> 1;
190 if (historySize > ((UInt32) 2 << 30))
191 sizeReserv = historySize >> 2;
192 sizeReserv += (keepAddBufferBefore + matchMaxLen + keepAddBufferAfter) / 2 + (1 << 19);
193
194 p->keepSizeBefore = historySize + keepAddBufferBefore + 1;
195 p->keepSizeAfter = matchMaxLen + keepAddBufferAfter;
196 /* we need one additional byte, since we use MoveBlock after pos++ and before dictionary using */
197 if (LzInWindow_Create(p, sizeReserv, alloc))
198 {
199 UInt32 newCyclicBufferSize = historySize + 1;
200 UInt32 hs;
201 p->matchMaxLen = matchMaxLen;
202 {
203 p->fixedHashSize = 0;
204 if (p->numHashBytes == 2)
205 hs = (1 << 16) - 1;
206 else
207 {
208 hs = historySize - 1;
209 hs |= (hs >> 1);
210 hs |= (hs >> 2);
211 hs |= (hs >> 4);
212 hs |= (hs >> 8);
213 hs >>= 1;
214 hs |= 0xFFFF; /* don't change it! It's required for Deflate */
215 if (hs > (1 << 24))
216 {
217 if (p->numHashBytes == 3)
218 hs = (1 << 24) - 1;
219 else
220 hs >>= 1;
221 }
222 }
223 p->hashMask = hs;
224 hs++;
225 if (p->numHashBytes > 2)
226 p->fixedHashSize += kHash2Size;
227 if (p->numHashBytes > 3)
228 p->fixedHashSize += kHash3Size;
229 if (p->numHashBytes > 4)
230 p->fixedHashSize += kHash4Size;
231 hs += p->fixedHashSize;
232 }
233
234 {
235 UInt32 prevSize = p->hashSizeSum + p->numSons;
236 UInt32 newSize;
237 p->historySize = historySize;
238 p->hashSizeSum = hs;
239 p->cyclicBufferSize = newCyclicBufferSize;
240 p->numSons = (p->btMode ? newCyclicBufferSize * 2 : newCyclicBufferSize);
241 newSize = p->hashSizeSum + p->numSons;
242 if (p->hash != 0 && prevSize == newSize)
243 return 1;
244 MatchFinder_FreeThisClassMemory(p, alloc);
245 p->hash = AllocRefs(newSize, alloc);
246 if (p->hash != 0)
247 {
248 p->son = p->hash + p->hashSizeSum;
249 return 1;
250 }
251 }
252 }
253 MatchFinder_Free(p, alloc);
254 return 0;
255}
256
257static void MatchFinder_SetLimits(CMatchFinder *p)
258{
259 UInt32 limit = kMaxValForNormalize - p->pos;
260 UInt32 limit2 = p->cyclicBufferSize - p->cyclicBufferPos;
261 if (limit2 < limit)
262 limit = limit2;
263 limit2 = p->streamPos - p->pos;
264 if (limit2 <= p->keepSizeAfter)
265 {
266 if (limit2 > 0)
267 limit2 = 1;
268 }
269 else
270 limit2 -= p->keepSizeAfter;
271 if (limit2 < limit)
272 limit = limit2;
273 {
274 UInt32 lenLimit = p->streamPos - p->pos;
275 if (lenLimit > p->matchMaxLen)
276 lenLimit = p->matchMaxLen;
277 p->lenLimit = lenLimit;
278 }
279 p->posLimit = p->pos + limit;
280}
281
282void MatchFinder_Init(CMatchFinder *p)
283{
284 UInt32 i;
285 for (i = 0; i < p->hashSizeSum; i++)
286 p->hash[i] = kEmptyHashValue;
287 p->cyclicBufferPos = 0;
288 p->buffer = p->bufferBase;
289 p->pos = p->streamPos = p->cyclicBufferSize;
290 p->result = SZ_OK;
291 p->streamEndWasReached = 0;
292 MatchFinder_ReadBlock(p);
293 MatchFinder_SetLimits(p);
294}
295
296static UInt32 MatchFinder_GetSubValue(CMatchFinder *p)
297{
298 return (p->pos - p->historySize - 1) & kNormalizeMask;
299}
300
301void MatchFinder_Normalize3(UInt32 subValue, CLzRef *items, UInt32 numItems)
302{
303 UInt32 i;
304 for (i = 0; i < numItems; i++)
305 {
306 UInt32 value = items[i];
307 if (value <= subValue)
308 value = kEmptyHashValue;
309 else
310 value -= subValue;
311 items[i] = value;
312 }
313}
314
315static void MatchFinder_Normalize(CMatchFinder *p)
316{
317 UInt32 subValue = MatchFinder_GetSubValue(p);
318 MatchFinder_Normalize3(subValue, p->hash, p->hashSizeSum + p->numSons);
319 MatchFinder_ReduceOffsets(p, subValue);
320}
321
322static void MatchFinder_CheckLimits(CMatchFinder *p)
323{
324 if (p->pos == kMaxValForNormalize)
325 MatchFinder_Normalize(p);
326 if (!p->streamEndWasReached && p->keepSizeAfter == p->streamPos - p->pos)
327 MatchFinder_CheckAndMoveAndRead(p);
328 if (p->cyclicBufferPos == p->cyclicBufferSize)
329 p->cyclicBufferPos = 0;
330 MatchFinder_SetLimits(p);
331}
332
333static UInt32 * Hc_GetMatchesSpec(UInt32 lenLimit, UInt32 curMatch, UInt32 pos, const Byte *cur, CLzRef *son, UInt32 _cyclicBufferPos,
334 UInt32 _cyclicBufferSize, UInt32 cutValue, UInt32 *distances, UInt32 maxLen)
335{
336 son[_cyclicBufferPos] = curMatch;
337 for (;;)
338 {
339 UInt32 delta = pos - curMatch;
340 if (cutValue-- == 0 || delta >= _cyclicBufferSize)
341 return distances;
342 {
343 const Byte *pb = cur - delta;
344 curMatch = son[_cyclicBufferPos - delta + ((delta > _cyclicBufferPos) ? _cyclicBufferSize : 0)];
345 if (pb[maxLen] == cur[maxLen] && *pb == *cur)
346 {
347 UInt32 len = 0;
348 while (++len != lenLimit)
349 if (pb[len] != cur[len])
350 break;
351 if (maxLen < len)
352 {
353 *distances++ = maxLen = len;
354 *distances++ = delta - 1;
355 if (len == lenLimit)
356 return distances;
357 }
358 }
359 }
360 }
361}
362
363UInt32 * GetMatchesSpec1(UInt32 lenLimit, UInt32 curMatch, UInt32 pos, const Byte *cur, CLzRef *son, UInt32 _cyclicBufferPos,
364 UInt32 _cyclicBufferSize, UInt32 cutValue, UInt32 *distances, UInt32 maxLen)
365{
366 CLzRef *ptr0 = son + (_cyclicBufferPos << 1) + 1;
367 CLzRef *ptr1 = son + (_cyclicBufferPos << 1);
368 UInt32 len0 = 0, len1 = 0;
369 for (;;)
370 {
371 UInt32 delta = pos - curMatch;
372 if (cutValue-- == 0 || delta >= _cyclicBufferSize)
373 {
374 *ptr0 = *ptr1 = kEmptyHashValue;
375 return distances;
376 }
377 {
378 CLzRef *pair = son + ((_cyclicBufferPos - delta + ((delta > _cyclicBufferPos) ? _cyclicBufferSize : 0)) << 1);
379 const Byte *pb = cur - delta;
380 UInt32 len = (len0 < len1 ? len0 : len1);
381 if (pb[len] == cur[len])
382 {
383 if (++len != lenLimit && pb[len] == cur[len])
384 while (++len != lenLimit)
385 if (pb[len] != cur[len])
386 break;
387 if (maxLen < len)
388 {
389 *distances++ = maxLen = len;
390 *distances++ = delta - 1;
391 if (len == lenLimit)
392 {
393 *ptr1 = pair[0];
394 *ptr0 = pair[1];
395 return distances;
396 }
397 }
398 }
399 if (pb[len] < cur[len])
400 {
401 *ptr1 = curMatch;
402 ptr1 = pair + 1;
403 curMatch = *ptr1;
404 len1 = len;
405 }
406 else
407 {
408 *ptr0 = curMatch;
409 ptr0 = pair;
410 curMatch = *ptr0;
411 len0 = len;
412 }
413 }
414 }
415}
416
417static void SkipMatchesSpec(UInt32 lenLimit, UInt32 curMatch, UInt32 pos, const Byte *cur, CLzRef *son, UInt32 _cyclicBufferPos,
418 UInt32 _cyclicBufferSize, UInt32 cutValue)
419{
420 CLzRef *ptr0 = son + (_cyclicBufferPos << 1) + 1;
421 CLzRef *ptr1 = son + (_cyclicBufferPos << 1);
422 UInt32 len0 = 0, len1 = 0;
423 for (;;)
424 {
425 UInt32 delta = pos - curMatch;
426 if (cutValue-- == 0 || delta >= _cyclicBufferSize)
427 {
428 *ptr0 = *ptr1 = kEmptyHashValue;
429 return;
430 }
431 {
432 CLzRef *pair = son + ((_cyclicBufferPos - delta + ((delta > _cyclicBufferPos) ? _cyclicBufferSize : 0)) << 1);
433 const Byte *pb = cur - delta;
434 UInt32 len = (len0 < len1 ? len0 : len1);
435 if (pb[len] == cur[len])
436 {
437 while (++len != lenLimit)
438 if (pb[len] != cur[len])
439 break;
440 {
441 if (len == lenLimit)
442 {
443 *ptr1 = pair[0];
444 *ptr0 = pair[1];
445 return;
446 }
447 }
448 }
449 if (pb[len] < cur[len])
450 {
451 *ptr1 = curMatch;
452 ptr1 = pair + 1;
453 curMatch = *ptr1;
454 len1 = len;
455 }
456 else
457 {
458 *ptr0 = curMatch;
459 ptr0 = pair;
460 curMatch = *ptr0;
461 len0 = len;
462 }
463 }
464 }
465}
466
467#define MOVE_POS \
468 ++p->cyclicBufferPos; \
469 p->buffer++; \
470 if (++p->pos == p->posLimit) MatchFinder_CheckLimits(p);
471
472#define MOVE_POS_RET MOVE_POS return offset;
473
474static void MatchFinder_MovePos(CMatchFinder *p)
475{
476 MOVE_POS;
477}
478
479#define GET_MATCHES_HEADER2(minLen, ret_op) \
480 UInt32 lenLimit; UInt32 hashValue; const Byte *cur; UInt32 curMatch; \
481 lenLimit = p->lenLimit; { if (lenLimit < minLen) { MatchFinder_MovePos(p); ret_op; }} \
482 cur = p->buffer;
483
484#define GET_MATCHES_HEADER(minLen) GET_MATCHES_HEADER2(minLen, return 0)
485#define SKIP_HEADER(minLen) GET_MATCHES_HEADER2(minLen, continue)
486
487#define MF_PARAMS(p) p->pos, p->buffer, p->son, p->cyclicBufferPos, p->cyclicBufferSize, p->cutValue
488
489#define GET_MATCHES_FOOTER(offset, maxLen) \
490 offset = (UInt32)(GetMatchesSpec1(lenLimit, curMatch, MF_PARAMS(p), \
491 distances + offset, maxLen) - distances); MOVE_POS_RET;
492
493#define SKIP_FOOTER \
494 SkipMatchesSpec(lenLimit, curMatch, MF_PARAMS(p)); MOVE_POS;
495
496static UInt32 Bt2_MatchFinder_GetMatches(CMatchFinder *p, UInt32 *distances)
497{
498 UInt32 offset;
499 GET_MATCHES_HEADER(2)
500 HASH2_CALC;
501 curMatch = p->hash[hashValue];
502 p->hash[hashValue] = p->pos;
503 offset = 0;
504 GET_MATCHES_FOOTER(offset, 1)
505}

507UInt32 Bt3Zip_MatchFinder_GetMatches(CMatchFinder *p, UInt32 *distances)
508{
509 UInt32 offset;
510 GET_MATCHES_HEADER(3)
511 HASH_ZIP_CALC;
512 curMatch = p->hash[hashValue];
513 p->hash[hashValue] = p->pos;
514 offset = 0;
515 GET_MATCHES_FOOTER(offset, 2)
516}
517
518static UInt32 Bt3_MatchFinder_GetMatches(CMatchFinder *p, UInt32 *distances)
519{
520 UInt32 hash2Value, delta2, maxLen, offset;
521 GET_MATCHES_HEADER(3)
522
523 HASH3_CALC;
524
525 delta2 = p->pos - p->hash[hash2Value];
526 curMatch = p->hash[kFix3HashSize + hashValue];
527
528 p->hash[hash2Value] = p->hash[kFix3HashSize + hashValue] = p->pos;
529
530 maxLen = 2;
531 offset = 0;
532 if (delta2 < p->cyclicBufferSize && *(cur - delta2) == *cur)
533 {
534 for (; maxLen != lenLimit; maxLen++)
535 if (cur[(ptrdiff_t) maxLen - delta2] != cur[maxLen])
536 break;
537 distances[0] = maxLen;
538 distances[1] = delta2 - 1;
539 offset = 2;
540 if (maxLen == lenLimit)
541 {
542 SkipMatchesSpec(lenLimit, curMatch, MF_PARAMS(p));
543 MOVE_POS_RET;
544 }
545 }
546 GET_MATCHES_FOOTER(offset, maxLen)
547}
548
549static UInt32 Bt4_MatchFinder_GetMatches(CMatchFinder *p, UInt32 *distances)
550{
551 UInt32 hash2Value, hash3Value, delta2, delta3, maxLen, offset;
552 GET_MATCHES_HEADER(4)
553
554 HASH4_CALC;
555
556 delta2 = p->pos - p->hash[hash2Value];
557 delta3 = p->pos - p->hash[kFix3HashSize + hash3Value];
558 curMatch = p->hash[kFix4HashSize + hashValue];
559
560 p->hash[hash2Value] = p->hash[kFix3HashSize + hash3Value] = p->hash[kFix4HashSize + hashValue] = p->pos;
561
562 maxLen = 1;
563 offset = 0;
564 if (delta2 < p->cyclicBufferSize && *(cur - delta2) == *cur)
565 {
566 distances[0] = maxLen = 2;
567 distances[1] = delta2 - 1;
568 offset = 2;
569 }
570 if (delta2 != delta3 && delta3 < p->cyclicBufferSize && *(cur - delta3) == *cur)
571 {
572 maxLen = 3;
573 distances[offset + 1] = delta3 - 1;
574 offset += 2;
575 delta2 = delta3;
576 }
577 if (offset != 0)
578 {
579 for (; maxLen != lenLimit; maxLen++)
580 if (cur[(ptrdiff_t) maxLen - delta2] != cur[maxLen])
581 break;
582 distances[offset - 2] = maxLen;
583 if (maxLen == lenLimit)
584 {
585 SkipMatchesSpec(lenLimit, curMatch, MF_PARAMS(p));
586 MOVE_POS_RET;
587 }
588 }
589 if (maxLen < 3)
590 maxLen = 3;
591 GET_MATCHES_FOOTER(offset, maxLen)
592}

594static UInt32 Hc4_MatchFinder_GetMatches(CMatchFinder *p, UInt32 *distances)
595{
596 UInt32 hash2Value, hash3Value, delta2, delta3, maxLen, offset;
597 GET_MATCHES_HEADER(4)
598
599 HASH4_CALC;
600
601 delta2 = p->pos - p->hash[hash2Value];
602 delta3 = p->pos - p->hash[kFix3HashSize + hash3Value];
603 curMatch = p->hash[kFix4HashSize + hashValue];
604
605 p->hash[hash2Value] = p->hash[kFix3HashSize + hash3Value] = p->hash[kFix4HashSize + hashValue] = p->pos;
606
607 maxLen = 1;
608 offset = 0;
609 if (delta2 < p->cyclicBufferSize && *(cur - delta2) == *cur)
610 {
611 distances[0] = maxLen = 2;
612 distances[1] = delta2 - 1;
613 offset = 2;
614 }
615 if (delta2 != delta3 && delta3 < p->cyclicBufferSize && *(cur - delta3) == *cur)
616 {
617 maxLen = 3;
618 distances[offset + 1] = delta3 - 1;
619 offset += 2;
620 delta2 = delta3;
621 }
622 if (offset != 0)
623 {
624 for (; maxLen != lenLimit; maxLen++)
625 if (cur[(ptrdiff_t) maxLen - delta2] != cur[maxLen])
626 break;
627 distances[offset - 2] = maxLen;
628 if (maxLen == lenLimit)
629 {
630 p->son[p->cyclicBufferPos] = curMatch;
631 MOVE_POS_RET;
632 }
633 }
634 if (maxLen < 3)
635 maxLen = 3;
636 offset = (UInt32) (Hc_GetMatchesSpec(lenLimit, curMatch, MF_PARAMS(p),
637 distances + offset, maxLen) - (distances));
638 MOVE_POS_RET
639}

641UInt32 Hc3Zip_MatchFinder_GetMatches(CMatchFinder *p, UInt32 *distances)

643 UInt32 offset;

647 p->hash[hashValue] = p->pos;
648 offset = (UInt32) (Hc_GetMatchesSpec(lenLimit, curMatch, MF_PARAMS(p),
649 distances, 2) - (distances));
650 MOVE_POS_RET
651}

731void MatchFinder_CreateVTable(CMatchFinder *p, IMatchFinder *vTable)
732{
733 vTable->Init = (Mf_Init_Func) MatchFinder_Init;
734 vTable->GetIndexByte = (Mf_GetIndexByte_Func) MatchFinder_GetIndexByte;
735 vTable->GetNumAvailableBytes = (Mf_GetNumAvailableBytes_Func) MatchFinder_GetNumAvailableBytes;
736 vTable->GetPointerToCurrentPos = (Mf_GetPointerToCurrentPos_Func) MatchFinder_GetPointerToCurrentPos;
737 if (!p->btMode)
738 {
739 vTable->GetMatches = (Mf_GetMatches_Func) Hc4_MatchFinder_GetMatches;
740 vTable->Skip = (Mf_Skip_Func) Hc4_MatchFinder_Skip;
741 }
742 else if (p->numHashBytes == 2)
743 {
744 vTable->GetMatches = (Mf_GetMatches_Func) Bt2_MatchFinder_GetMatches;
745 vTable->Skip = (Mf_Skip_Func) Bt2_MatchFinder_Skip;
746 }
747 else if (p->numHashBytes == 3)
748 {
749 vTable->GetMatches = (Mf_GetMatches_Func) Bt3_MatchFinder_GetMatches;
750 vTable->Skip = (Mf_Skip_Func) Bt3_MatchFinder_Skip;
751 }
752 else
753 {
754 vTable->GetMatches = (Mf_GetMatches_Func) Bt4_MatchFinder_GetMatches;
